.th GWCUR VII 19-March-1980
.sh NAME
gwcur \*- write a cursor to a GRINNELL window
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd gwcur
(area, curnum, col, row, onoff, color)
.s3
int area[16];
.br
int curnum;
.br
int col;
.br
int row;
.br
int onoff;
.br
int color;
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Gwcur
is used to manipulate the cursors  in  a GRINNELL window.
The  selected  cursor will be written to window-relative position
.it (col,row).
In addition, the cursor can be turned on or off  when
it  is  positioned  and  the color can be selected to be black or
white. When using this function, care should  be  taken  that  no
other user is manipulating the same cursor.
.s1
.it Area
is the buffer used in the
.it gopen
call.
.it Curnum
indicates which cursor, 1 or 2, is to be written.
If
.it onoff
is non-zero, the cursor will be visible, if it is zero, the cursor will be
invisible.  The cursor color is white if
.it color
is non-zero and black of
.it color
is zero.
.s3
The value returned is zero on success, non-zero on failure.
